  "read": "On raw per-device log lines, Ascend and AMD look similar: about 70-74 TFLOPs per Ascend die versus 74-77 TFLOPs per MI350. That is misleading for the user's memory-equivalent comparison because the Ascend box has 16 compute dies. At the memory-equivalent node level, existing Ascend runs deliver about 45-47k tokens/s versus the best current 4xMI350 candidate at about 16.4k tokens/s. With the same AMD FLOPs/token accounting, Ascend maps to about 214-224 TFLOPs per MI350-equivalent, while AMD is about 77 TFLOPs/GPU. So current AMD is roughly 34-36% of the observed Ascend memory-equivalent throughput and needs about 2.8-2.9x to match these local Ascend runs, or about 3.6x to hit the active 277 TFLOPs/GPU target.",
